																		ADMIN POST // AUTHOR POST
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/dexanote" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(481882); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=481882&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610183045" alt="Dexanote" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=481882)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/dexanote" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(481882); return false;" >Dexanote</a></span> <span class="odate time_1581903222 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">17 Feb 2020 01:33</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4503775">
									

<p>Gonna choose this post to reply to a little over 8 years later. Struck me that I should, considering the circumstances.</p>
<p>All 'in-game dialogue' in this Tale is retrofitted from the video game 'Pokemon RED version' as presented and published on the Nintendo Game Boy handheld video game console.</p>
<p>All material was found freely online, I'm 90% sure through Bulbapedia but possibly through a full script of the game, as well as specific lines (really, clarification of how battle dialogue is structured) taken from a full playthrough video series since lost on Youtube.</p>
<p>All dialogue taken from the game is originates from Pokemon RED version (not the remakes) and is intended for parody, and for the most part is not original to me. Some has been altered for comedy's sake or to better flow with the Tale's structure.</p>

							</div>

								
					
